  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for python36",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python36 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2025-6075: quadratic complexity in `os.path.expandvars()` can lead to performance degradation when values passed\n  to it are user-controlled (bsc#1252974).\n- CVE-2025-8291: lack of validity checks on the ZIP64 End of Central Directory (EOCD) record allows for the creation of\n  ZIP archives that are processed inconsistently by the `zipfile` module (bsc#1251305).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
